  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Family learning - improving school enrolments and promoting women&apos;s empowerment (South Sudan)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant is to trial the concept of Family Learning in five schools within Mundri region in South Sudan. Family Learning bridges the gap between school learning for children and the adult literacy offered to their parents, mostly mothers and grandmothers, through REFLECT literacy groups. Most families in the target communities are illiterate, with no reading matter at home. Primary school completion rates are 12% for boys, 9% for girls. The project will address this problem through workshops to draw parents, pupils and teachers together to introduce Family Learning, to develop low cost resources, and support their children in school. It will test Family Learning as a new way forward.</narrative>
  </description>
